Build a real estate apartment listing website that runs locally on my laptop/private machine. Here are the full requirements:

--- TECH STACK ---
- Frontend: plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Backend: Node.js with Express
- Database: MySQL (running locally)
- The app should run on http://localhost:3000

--- DATABASE ---
Create a MySQL database called "realestate_db" with a table called "apartments" containing these columns:
  id (INT, auto-increment, primary key)
  title (VARCHAR)
  bhk (INT — number of bedrooms, e.g. 1, 2, 3, 4)
  rent_price (DECIMAL — monthly rent in INR)
  sale_price (DECIMAL — sale price in INR, nullable)
  locality (VARCHAR)
  city (VARCHAR)
  area_sqft (INT)
  floor_number (INT)
  total_floors (INT)
  furnished_status (ENUM: 'furnished', 'semi-furnished', 'unfurnished')
  available_from (DATE)
  description (TEXT)
  contact_name (VARCHAR)
  contact_phone (VARCHAR)
  created_at (TIMESTAMP, default CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)

Also provide:
  - SQL script to create the database and table
  - SQL script to insert at least 12 sample listings covering 1BHK, 2BHK, 3BHK, and 4BHK across different price ranges

--- BACKEND API ---
Build a REST API with these endpoints:
  GET  /api/apartments        — list all apartments (supports query params for bhk, city, min_price, max_price)
  GET  /api/apartments/:id    — get single apartment details
  POST /api/apartments        — add a new listing
  PUT  /api/apartments/:id    — update a listing
  DELETE /api/apartments/:id  — delete a listing

--- FRONTEND ---
Build a clean, modern apartment listing website with:
  1. A homepage showing all apartment cards in a grid layout
  2. Each card shows: BHK type, title, locality, price, area (sqft), furnished status, and a "View Details" button
  3. A detail page/modal showing all apartment information
  4. A clear badge or tag showing the BHK type (1BHK, 2BHK etc.) prominently on each card

--- EXTRA FEATURES ---
   1. Filter by BHK (1BHK, 2BHK, 3BHK, 4BHK+)
   2. Price range filter (min/max slider)
   3. Search by locality or city

--- LOCAL SETUP ---
Provide a complete step-by-step guide to:
  1. Set up MySQL locally and create the database
  2. Install all dependencies
  3. Configure the database connection (host: localhost, port: 3306)
  4. Start the backend server on port 3000
  5. Open the website in a browser at http://localhost:3000

Make the code production-quality with proper error handling, environment variables (.env file) for DB credentials, and clear folder structure. Include a README.md with setup instructions.
